organic_results.title: Interregional migration and the education of American scientists
organic_results.snippet: An analysis of the interregional migration undertaken for purposes of higher education by a recent cohort of American scientists with doctoral degrees indicates that the quality reputation of educational institutions within a region is a major force of attraction. The aggregate of individuals who migrate for their education attend institutions which exhibit a higher than average quality rating.
